@startuml
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
title Where credentials live and the layers that protect them

actor Attacker

package "Normal world (VTL0)" {
  [User session] as USER
  node "LSASS process" {
    [Cached secrets\n(NT hash, TGT,\nWDigest cleartext)] as SECRETS
    [LSA (interface)] as LSA
  }
}

package "Secure world (VTL1) -- VBS" {
  [LSAIso\n(isolated LSA)] as LSAISO
  [Secrets vault] as VAULT
}

USER --> LSA
LSA ..> LSAISO : RPC (Credential Guard on)
LSAISO --> VAULT

Attacker ..> SECRETS : (1) dump LSASS\n(mimikatz)
note right of SECRETS
  Defenses, weakest to strongest:
  - Disable WDigest -> no cleartext
  - RunAsPPL -> blocks user-mode debug
    (bypassable by a signed kernel driver)
  - Credential Guard -> secrets move to
    VTL1; LSASS no longer holds them
end note

Attacker ..> LSAISO : (2) blocked by\nVBS isolation
@enduml
